o trivial unit tests) is removed. The coordinator's `spawn_http_receiver` already reimplements the same polling loop with deduplication — `receiver.rs` is dead code.\n\n### Step 3: Remove re-exports from `lib.rs`\n\n**File: `crates/reme-transport/src/lib.rs`**\n\n- Remove `pub mod receiver;` (line 15)\n- Remove the `#[allow(deprecated)]` + `pub use receiver::{MessageReceiver, ReceiverConfig, ReceiverHandle};` block (lines 44–45)\n\n### Step 4: Update `app.rs` coordinator construction\n\n**File: `apps/client/src/tui/app.rs`**\n\nReplace (lines 24, 537–541):\n```rust\n#[allow(deprecated)]\nuse reme_transport::{ReceiverConfig, ...};\n\n#[allow(deprecated)]\nlet coordinator_config = CoordinatorConfig {\n    receiver_config: ReceiverConfig::with_poll_interval(Duration::from_secs(2)),\n    ..CoordinatorConfig::default()\n};\n```\n\nWith:\n```rust\nlet coordinator_config = CoordinatorConfig {\n    poll_interval: Duration::from_secs(2),\n    ..CoordinatorConfig::default()\n};\n```\n\nRemove `ReceiverConfig` from the import and the `#[allow(deprecated)]` annotations.\n\n### Step 5: Remove stale `#[allow(deprecated)]` from `config.rs`\n\n**File: `apps/client/src/config.rs`** (line 598)\n\nRemove `#[allow(deprecated)]` on `RawConfig` — it's stale (no deprecated types are used in that struct).\n\n### Step 6: Migrate integration tests from `MessageReceiver` to `TransportCoordinator`\n\n**File: `crates/reme-core/tests/integration.rs`**\n\nThree test functions use `MessageReceiver::new(pool).subscribe(routing_key, config)`. Replace each with `TransportCoordinator`:\n\n```rust\n// Before:\nlet receiver = MessageReceiver::new(transport.clone());\nlet config = ReceiverConfig::with_poll_interval(Duration::from_millis(50));\nlet (mut events, _handle) = receiver.subscribe(bob.routing_key(), config);\n\n// After:\nlet mut coordinator = TransportCoordinator::new(CoordinatorConfig {\n    poll_interval: Duration::from_millis(50),\n    ..CoordinatorConfig::default()\n});\ncoordinator.set_htt